article.headline: Utah Valley St. 86, N.J. Tech 55
article.story: OREM, Utah (AP) -- Ryan Toolson scored 28 points to lead Utah Valley State to a 86-55 win over New Jersey Tech on Thursday night. Toolson scored 22 points over the final 10 minutes of the first half to lead the Wolverines (14-7). The Highlanders (3-17) led by one point midway through the first half before Toolson started a 35-12 run for UVSC. Utah Valley State trailed 13-12 with 11 minutes remaining in the first half, then Toolson hit five consecutive 3-pointers. Toolson added another 3-pointer and four free throws and UVSC led 50-27 at halftime. Kraig Peters led the Highlanders with 15 points. Nesho Milosevic added 10 points and 11 rebounds for New Jersey Tech. David Heck had 13 points and eight assists for the Wolverines.
